  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. These typically include:\n\n1. Financial institutions must report suspicious transactions\n2. Businesses must have anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n3. Professionals like bankers and lawyers have mandatory reporting obligations\n4. Suspicious Activity Reports (SARs) must be filed with relevant authorities\n5. Penalties exist for failing to report suspected money laundering\n\nHowever, I cannot provide specific legal advice about reporting requirements. For detailed guidance, consult a legal professional familiar with regulations in your jurisdiction.",
